<br>
Just a couple of ideas tho.  <br>
<br>
1) You didnt mention a reagent fee.  Dunno, does that sound better than entrance fee?  heh.  I would suggest going with the numbers I mentioned last night for the reason discussed.  However, it is up to you.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) I'm really not sure if this will make any difference, but I would suggest that any caster that dies during the battle and comes back in, mem not only their damage spell, but also RM if they have it and cast it on themselves before entering combat again.  It shouldnt take more than an extra 10-15 seconds to do this and it might keep the caster from being feared once or twice.  With Vox had half the casters been feared just 1 less time, we probably would have taken her down.  Because you lose all buffs and gear when you die, this would be the only resists you're wearing when going in.<br>
<br>
3) I dont really have a point 3, but I thought this would look silly with just 2 things.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I would also like to restress Kommisar's point about tanks making sure you have the proper resistances.  Unlike casters you cannot come on back in if you die.  And if the tanks die, then we will lose.  Period.  There is no way that the casters can take down a dragon without tanks to protect them.  You must live for as long as possible.  Please do not skimp on them thinking you'll be the only one to do so.  Low resistances are one of the things that have run many guilds/alliances and even CoG into trouble before with these large target mobs.  Resists are everything, above and beyond even ac and atk and str.  For tanks on these raids, everything else is pretty much secondary.  Remember, what kills you isnt their physical attacks so much as their AoE spells and Fear.  <br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Druid, 52, De-Caffienated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Ack!<br>
